        temp = nums[i] 
        nums[i] = nums[j]
        nums[j] = temp
  return nums
```
This code now sorts the input list `nums` in ascending order. The reason it works is because the inner loop checks whether the current element is smaller than the next one (if `nums[i] < nums[j]`). If so, it swaps them, ensuring that the smallest elements "bubble" up to the front of the list.

